can't have a baby by nature.

333
00:39:59,250 --> 00:40:01,625
It is obvious that your son
is having a problem.

334
00:40:05,541 --> 00:40:09,916
If you really love your son,
you should give him a chance.

335
00:40:11,416 --> 00:40:14,458
Perhaps the boy
doesn't want something special,

336
00:40:15,583 --> 00:40:18,708
just the same things as his friends.

337
00:40:22,708 --> 00:40:23,958
What's next?

338
00:40:25,000 --> 00:40:26,041
Phoon…

339
00:40:28,791 --> 00:40:31,333
Just let him spend time with his mom,

340
00:40:32,500 --> 00:40:35,208
a week or two,

341
00:40:35,958 --> 00:40:38,458
then come back to stay with you.

342
00:40:39,416 --> 00:40:43,083
I believe it will help fulfill
what he longs for.

343
00:40:43,166 --> 00:40:44,666
This is clearly selfish.

344
00:40:47,666 --> 00:40:49,625
You'd better be more generous.

345
00:40:51,083 --> 00:40:53,041
And this is your son we're talking about.

346
00:40:58,250 --> 00:40:59,750
He just wants to have a mother.

347
00:41:01,208 --> 00:41:04,583
Not every orphan is lucky
enough to find his birth mother.

348
00:41:09,541 --> 00:41:13,750
And how could I be sure you
won't abandon him again?

349
00:41:19,416 --> 00:41:23,666
Losing my little kid
is more than enough already.

350
00:41:28,125 --> 00:41:29,958
I just want to see him

351
00:41:32,333 --> 00:41:34,875
to make up for what I had done.

352
00:41:40,875 --> 00:41:44,458
How would you explain how he was born?

353
00:41:45,208 --> 00:41:49,708
He will learn from school when it's time.
And he'll understand.

354
00:41:52,083 --> 00:41:55,333
And how would you describe
your relationship?

355
00:42:03,541 --> 00:42:05,666
Being homosexual is not wrong.

356
00:42:07,166 --> 00:42:10,083
But if there are choices,

357
00:42:10,458 --> 00:42:13,416
I believe no one
would want a kid to be gay.

358
00:42:16,416 --> 00:42:19,833
I think, deep inside,
you are also afraid, aren't you?

359
00:42:33,583 --> 00:42:34,666
Yes?

360
00:42:38,791 --> 00:42:40,416
Yes, yes. I'll be there.

361
00:42:49,083 --> 00:42:50,625
You don't need to come.

362
00:42:52,125 --> 00:42:53,166
I'm all right.

363
00:42:56,041 --> 00:42:58,000
Your friend told me you fell down.

364
00:42:59,041 --> 00:43:01,791
I was just dancing as usual.

365
00:43:02,583 --> 00:43:04,416
Falling down when dancing is normal.

366
00:43:06,208 --> 00:43:08,166
You have to be more careful.

367
00:43:09,458 --> 00:43:11,500
No wonder why Mom left.

368
00:43:12,583 --> 00:43:13,750
Yes,

369
00:43:14,750 --> 00:43:16,541
I was too late.

370
00:43:17,458 --> 00:43:18,875
Unlike both of you.

371
00:43:20,208 --> 00:43:21,875
He is just worried about you.

372
00:43:22,958 --> 00:43:24,708
Take good care of yourself, though.

373
00:43:26,416 --> 00:43:28,375
It's like you're not accustomed to me.

374
00:43:29,083 --> 00:43:30,416
I raised you.

375
00:43:32,291 --> 00:43:34,541
Sometimes, being accustomed is harmful.

376
00:43:35,125 --> 00:43:36,458
It makes us unprepared.

377
00:43:38,208 --> 00:43:39,666
Just use protection.

378
00:43:40,208 --> 00:43:42,000
You're over 30 now.

379
00:43:42,083 --> 00:43:44,000
I'm not talking about that.

380
00:43:45,291 --> 00:43:48,208
I know, you're talking about Butr.

381
00:43:52,416 --> 00:43:55,583
I'm sorry for what I am.

382
00:43:57,291 --> 00:44:02,250
I feel guilty about you and also your mom.

383
00:44:03,541 --> 00:44:10,291
I'm sorry for being the main reason
that you became like me.

384
00:44:12,291 --> 00:44:13,833
But what can I do?

385
00:44:14,916 --> 00:44:19,000
I've tried not to chitchat with Butr,

386
00:44:22,250 --> 00:44:26,833
because I know you're afraid. So am I.

387
00:44:31,166 --> 00:44:35,125
Go… I'm going to sleep.

388
00:44:40,458 --> 00:44:41,750
Just go.

389
00:44:47,750 --> 00:44:48,708
Goodnight, Dad.

390
00:44:53,083 --> 00:44:54,583
Turn off the light.

391
00:45:40,625 --> 00:45:41,750
Thank you.

392
00:45:44,708 --> 00:45:45,875
I did it for my son.

393
00:46:55,875 --> 00:46:57,500
He's easygoing, isn't he?

394
00:47:00,875 --> 00:47:02,000
Of course. He wants to have a mother.

395
00:47:07,250 --> 00:47:10,750
I meant to make you feel okay

396
00:47:12,083 --> 00:47:16,916
that our son is friendly
and can understand things easily.

397
00:47:20,458 --> 00:47:21,750
I hope so,

398
00:47:22,833 --> 00:47:26,791
because I'm not sure
if I'm right or wrong.

399
00:47:36,375 --> 00:47:41,000
At first, I didn't agree
with you letting them in.

400
00:47:44,083 --> 00:47:45,666
But when I see him smile,

401
00:47:47,416 --> 00:47:49,416
my prejudice is gone.

402
00:47:55,541 --> 00:47:57,000
Because we are his fathers.

403
00:48:23,875 --> 00:48:25,208
Butr,

404
00:48:26,708 --> 00:48:27,750
let's take a shower together.

405
00:48:29,666 --> 00:48:31,250
No, I'm grown now!

406
00:49:26,041 --> 00:49:27,208
What's the matter?

407
00:49:29,250 --> 00:49:30,458
Butr might come in.

408
00:49:37,291 --> 00:49:38,166
He's sleeping.

409
00:49:40,500 --> 00:49:45,750
Don't you notice
that he's acting strangely?

410
00:49:46,791 --> 00:49:48,416
Is that because of that family?

411
00:49:50,208 --> 00:49:53,291
He's been strange
since we came back from the beach.

412
00:49:54,125 --> 00:49:58,291
He doesn't let us go into the school
or have a shower with him.

413
00:50:01,750 --> 00:50:05,500
Are you too worried?

414
00:50:07,375 --> 00:50:11,791
Kids at this age normally think
they are grown up.

415
00:50:12,416 --> 00:50:15,541
Exactly. The more he grows,
the more careful we have to be.

416
00:50:16,333 --> 00:50:18,083
We'll be in trouble if he comes in.

417
00:50:18,708 --> 00:50:20,791
Last time, he found the lube in the bag.

418
00:50:21,750 --> 00:50:23,208
I'm worried.

419
00:50:27,916 --> 00:50:30,458
He just gets naughtier as he grows up.

420
00:50:34,916 --> 00:50:41,041
But I'm certainly naughtier.

421
00:50:48,166 --> 00:50:50,208
Shall we try to behave
like we are friends?

422
00:50:50,791 --> 00:50:52,750
