452
00:53:28,916 --> 00:53:30,250
Butr touched mine, too.

453
00:53:30,333 --> 00:53:31,500
Mine too.

454
00:53:43,125 --> 00:53:45,083
Can I stay here?

455
00:53:46,500 --> 00:53:49,000
You said you wanted
to have a mother, didn't you?

456
00:53:50,833 --> 00:53:52,458
I wanna have a mother,

457
00:53:52,708 --> 00:53:55,250
but I don't want to leave Papi and Daddy.

458
00:53:58,000 --> 00:54:00,500
If I did something wrong, I'm sorry.

459
00:54:07,291 --> 00:54:08,458
Phoon…

460
00:54:09,208 --> 00:54:11,083
Papi, help me.

461
00:54:13,875 --> 00:54:15,166
Phoon... No.

462
00:54:20,791 --> 00:54:24,250
You become stubborn again.
Why is it so hard to please you?

463
00:54:25,791 --> 00:54:28,541
We've tried to be both father
and mother for you,

464
00:54:29,708 --> 00:54:31,500
but you still wanna have a mother.

465
00:54:32,541 --> 00:54:34,541
You found you own mother,
but you don't wanna go with her.

466
00:54:36,791 --> 00:54:38,666
What should I do to please you?

467
00:54:39,041 --> 00:54:40,375
I'm sorry.

468
00:54:40,583 --> 00:54:42,041
I'm guilty.

469
00:54:42,125 --> 00:54:44,125
I don't want anything.

470
00:54:46,208 --> 00:54:47,708
I don't wanna go.

471
00:55:03,416 --> 00:55:05,125
Are you sure you wanna do this?

472
00:55:11,750 --> 00:55:13,666
You're hurting our family.

473
00:55:16,666 --> 00:55:21,625
All of us will only regret it.

474
00:55:24,375 --> 00:55:26,083
I don't want to confuse him.

475
00:55:29,208 --> 00:55:31,375
I know it hurts to heal the wound,

476
00:55:32,708 --> 00:55:35,500
but it's better than waiting
until it's too late.

477
00:55:40,833 --> 00:55:42,083
Well said!

478
00:55:44,041 --> 00:55:45,708
-Don't you love him?
-I do.

479
00:55:46,416 --> 00:55:48,250
I don't want him to be a problem child.

480
00:55:48,333 --> 00:55:49,875
A problem child, or your problem?

481
00:55:50,416 --> 00:55:51,458
What do you mean?

482
00:55:52,250 --> 00:55:53,833
I'm acting for our son

483
00:55:54,541 --> 00:55:57,000
and trying to sustain our family.

484
00:55:57,083 --> 00:55:58,791
For him or for yourself?

485
00:56:00,916 --> 00:56:02,166
And most importantly,

486
00:56:04,916 --> 00:56:06,500
this is our family.

487
00:56:09,000 --> 00:56:11,833
Aren't you afraid
that he’ll become gay like us?

488
00:56:11,916 --> 00:56:14,291
Don't put your weakness on him.

489
00:56:17,708 --> 00:56:19,000
I won't let him go anywhere.

490
00:56:19,666 --> 00:56:20,666
But he is my son.

491
00:56:25,583 --> 00:56:26,583
That's right.

492
00:56:30,208 --> 00:56:32,083
Butr is a son only to you.

493
00:56:36,833 --> 00:56:40,666
What about my love for Butr?
Is it nothing to you?

494
00:57:06,041 --> 00:57:08,583
Daddy doesn't love me now?

495
00:57:11,500 --> 00:57:12,666
He does.

496
00:57:15,625 --> 00:57:17,541
But probably too much.

497
00:57:18,958 --> 00:57:22,625
What do you mean?
Too much? I don't understand.

498
00:57:31,333 --> 00:57:32,416
Let's sleep.

499
00:57:33,041 --> 00:57:34,666
You have to get up early tomorrow.

500
00:57:41,541 --> 00:57:46,041
I don't want to sleep
if I have to wake up and leave.

501
00:57:46,125 --> 00:57:50,500
I've never slept anywhere else
without Papi and Daddy.

502
00:57:50,708 --> 00:57:54,541
I'm scared. I know I'll miss you.

503
00:58:06,125 --> 00:58:07,458
So am I.

504
00:58:10,291 --> 00:58:12,833
Shall we run away and live with grandma?

505
00:59:18,583 --> 00:59:20,541
How were we born?

506
00:59:23,666 --> 00:59:29,208
We were born from the love
of a man and a woman.

507
00:59:30,791 --> 00:59:34,541
And when they have a baby,
they become father and mother.

508
00:59:34,625 --> 00:59:36,083
So, you have two fathers, don't you?

509
00:59:36,333 --> 00:59:38,208
Or your dad is a fag?

510
00:59:47,833 --> 00:59:49,458
What do you like to eat, Butr?

511
00:59:54,541 --> 00:59:56,125
I like fried chicken.

512
00:59:56,375 --> 00:59:59,041
Good. I'm good at frying chicken.

513
01:00:00,833 --> 01:00:03,750
Your Papi and Daddy told me
you wanted to play soccer.

514
01:00:03,833 --> 01:00:06,166
How about getting some soccer uniforms?

515
01:00:06,250 --> 01:00:08,416
And how about learning soccer
with Uncle Tiw?

516
01:00:08,750 --> 01:00:11,250
He was a soccer player at school.

517
01:00:12,000 --> 01:00:13,041
Really?

518
01:00:14,541 --> 01:00:15,583
Yes.

519
01:00:16,208 --> 01:00:19,250
But today, let's go
to the countryside first.

520
01:00:19,750 --> 01:00:20,666
Okay.

521
01:01:18,500 --> 01:01:19,625
What?

522
01:01:20,291 --> 01:01:22,041
Are you pregnant?

523
01:01:29,958 --> 01:01:31,125
How did you come in?

524
01:01:31,791 --> 01:01:32,708
Why didn't you ask for permission?

525
01:01:35,625 --> 01:01:40,458
You put your nose in our business
without asking for permission, too.

526
01:01:44,125 --> 01:01:45,500
That's because I felt sympathetic.

527
01:01:46,291 --> 01:01:47,625
You didn't have to.

528
01:01:48,875 --> 01:01:51,000
Just don't see us as abnormal ones.
