529
01:01:58,458 --> 01:02:00,708
I just tried to solve the problem instead.

530
01:02:05,625 --> 01:02:08,375
I insist that I truly understand him.

531
01:02:09,708 --> 01:02:11,708
You don't have to understand everything,

532
01:02:13,000 --> 01:02:14,166
especially others' business.

533
01:02:16,250 --> 01:02:18,875
You try to be a looking glass
reflecting others' sufferings,

534
01:02:21,000 --> 01:02:23,458
but never look at your meddling self.

535
01:02:32,583 --> 01:02:33,958
Daddy is busy.

536
01:02:39,625 --> 01:02:40,791
I love you, too.

537
01:02:41,708 --> 01:02:42,750
Sweet dreams.

538
01:02:46,458 --> 01:02:47,333
Is that Butr?

539
01:02:49,166 --> 01:02:50,416
How is he?

540
01:02:52,875 --> 01:02:54,375
You said he is your son.

541
01:02:55,500 --> 01:02:57,083
Call him if you want to know.

542
01:03:18,625 --> 01:03:19,791
-You missed!
-Tag him!

543
01:03:23,875 --> 01:03:25,041
Help me.

544
01:03:25,625 --> 01:03:26,541
Help.

545
01:03:42,333 --> 01:03:43,208
Here's your backpack.

546
01:03:48,333 --> 01:03:49,875
Good boy. Let's go.

547
01:04:14,833 --> 01:04:18,541
Butr, don't your Papi and Daddy
bring you here these days?

548
01:04:19,500 --> 01:04:23,541
My mom brought me!
Her boyfriend drove for me.

549
01:04:37,833 --> 01:04:39,541
Haven't you taken a shower yet, Tiw?

550
01:04:44,916 --> 01:04:46,041
Neither have you.

551
01:04:51,625 --> 01:04:52,791
Are you okay?

552
01:04:58,208 --> 01:04:59,500
I miss our son.

553
01:05:10,041 --> 01:05:11,750
I miss him too.

554
01:05:18,291 --> 01:05:22,041
But we're still lucky that we have Butr.

555
01:06:24,666 --> 01:06:25,708
Hello.

556
01:06:28,458 --> 01:06:30,750
What? It's due in two days, isn't it?

557
01:06:38,916 --> 01:06:40,333
Oh, I'm sorry.

558
01:06:40,833 --> 01:06:41,875
I thought it's Wednesday.

559
01:06:42,291 --> 01:06:43,708
I'll send it to you this evening.

560
01:07:14,791 --> 01:07:18,166
Mr. Phoon,
Did you sign it in the wrong place?

561
01:07:18,250 --> 01:07:20,750
This is for the other board member.

562
01:07:26,625 --> 01:07:28,833
Oh, I'm really sorry.

563
01:07:29,541 --> 01:07:30,708
Can you get me a new one?

564
01:07:31,250 --> 01:07:32,208
Yes.

565
01:07:32,916 --> 01:07:34,000
Thank you.

566
01:07:57,875 --> 01:07:59,041
Hello.

567
01:07:59,458 --> 01:08:00,583
Yes, Mr. Phoon.

568
01:08:02,250 --> 01:08:03,625
How is Butr doing?

569
01:08:04,750 --> 01:08:05,833
He's fine.

570
01:08:06,125 --> 01:08:07,583
He is well-adjusted.

571
01:08:08,208 --> 01:08:09,833
He's at school now.

572
01:08:10,583 --> 01:08:12,250
Do you want to talk with him?

573
01:08:12,583 --> 01:08:15,750
I'll tell him
to call you back this evening.

574
01:08:16,500 --> 01:08:17,541
That's fine.

575
01:08:18,583 --> 01:08:19,625
Thank you.

576
01:08:39,416 --> 01:08:43,791
THE BIBLE OF X

577
01:08:46,625 --> 01:08:49,041
Hey class,
do you know what next Monday is?

578
01:08:49,125 --> 01:08:52,500
It's Father's Day.

579
01:08:52,583 --> 01:08:54,375
That's correct.

580
01:08:55,625 --> 01:08:58,875
So today, let's make a card
for Father's day.

581
01:08:59,666 --> 01:09:00,916
Here you are.

582
01:09:01,250 --> 01:09:02,250
Yours.

583
01:09:04,041 --> 01:09:05,083
Good.

584
01:09:05,833 --> 01:09:06,833
And yours.

585
01:09:07,583 --> 01:09:08,708
That's right.

586
01:09:08,791 --> 01:09:09,875
This is yours.

587
01:09:10,708 --> 01:09:11,750
Here you go.

588
01:09:15,291 --> 01:09:16,375
Go ahead.

589
01:09:18,166 --> 01:09:19,333
Yes.

590
01:11:07,625 --> 01:11:11,458
The number you have dialed
cannot be connected.

591
01:13:55,708 --> 01:13:56,708
Butr,

592
01:13:58,791 --> 01:14:00,000
I'll be right back.

593
01:15:21,666 --> 01:15:22,791
What's wrong, Nan?

594
01:15:26,541 --> 01:15:27,791
Nothing.

595
01:15:28,333 --> 01:15:31,000
I just want to use the toilet.

596
01:16:29,583 --> 01:16:30,833
Hey! Who was it?

597
01:17:04,000 --> 01:17:08,083
I told you. A child is not like a puppy
that can be replaced.

598
01:17:08,166 --> 01:17:09,500
But he's my son.

599
01:17:16,916 --> 01:17:20,041
He's just curious like other boys.

600
01:17:20,500 --> 01:17:23,958
If we teach and give him some time,
he might be better.

601
01:17:25,333 --> 01:17:27,250
I have no idea
how that gay couple raised him.

602
01:19:18,000 --> 01:19:19,875
So, do you still want
to register our marriage?

603
01:19:22,250 --> 01:19:23,375
Nothing would change.

604
01:19:24,708 --> 01:19:26,416
It will neither make me
become a true father

605
01:19:28,125 --> 01:19:29,500
nor make you a good father.

606
01:19:30,958 --> 01:19:31,833
Wait.

607
01:19:31,916 --> 01:19:33,208
What do you mean?

608
01:19:34,916 --> 01:19:38,250
Everything I've done has been for our son.

609
01:19:39,916 --> 01:19:41,166
If you're so scared,

610
01:19:42,000 --> 01:19:43,541
you shouldn't have adopted him
in the first place.

611
01:19:48,500 --> 01:19:49,583
And what about this?

612
01:19:53,916 --> 01:19:55,791
The invitation letter for Father's Day.

613
01:19:56,625 --> 01:19:58,666
Why is it in the trash?

614
01:20:11,875 --> 01:20:13,416
I was afraid that when you see it,

615
01:20:16,291 --> 01:20:20,041
you would miss him
and wanna join the activity.

616
01:20:28,958 --> 01:20:30,125
I just realized

617
01:20:32,541 --> 01:20:34,375
that you're such a coward.

618
01:20:59,416 --> 01:21:04,083
Missing him means
that we love him so much.

619
01:21:11,791 --> 01:21:13,875
Letting him go with his mother

620
01:21:15,833 --> 01:21:18,458
doesn't mean we're no longer his fathers.

621
01:21:26,833 --> 01:21:28,500
Phoon! Phoon!

622
01:21:29,208 --> 01:21:30,083
Phoon!

623
01:21:30,166 --> 01:21:31,708
Phoon! Please don't.

624
01:21:31,791 --> 01:21:34,083
Phoon! Stop! Don't act like this!

625
01:21:34,291 --> 01:21:35,791
Phoon! Stop!

626
01:21:35,875 --> 01:21:36,916
Phoon!

627
01:21:38,291 --> 01:21:39,291
Phoon…

628
01:21:59,416 --> 01:22:00,625
It was my fault.

629
01:22:01,916 --> 01:22:03,791
I made everything worse.

630
01:22:05,875 --> 01:22:08,000
I never wanted to let him go.

631
01:22:14,166 --> 01:22:16,916
But… I was scared.

632
01:22:43,208 --> 01:22:48,291
It's the parents' responsibility
to raise their child,

633
01:22:50,833 --> 01:22:52,208
not to choose.

634
01:23:03,416 --> 01:23:05,833
Why didn't you bring me to my senses?

635
01:23:16,458 --> 01:23:18,625
Do I have the right to?

636
01:23:22,583 --> 01:23:25,291
I'm afraid you will say
he is your son again.

637
01:23:27,375 --> 01:23:30,416
You know, I didn't dare to talk
about him again since then.

638
01:23:39,750 --> 01:23:40,958
I'm sorry.

639
01:23:43,000 --> 01:23:44,208
I am a coward.

640
01:23:48,500 --> 01:23:49,791
I'm selfish.

641
01:23:57,916 --> 01:24:04,750
I don't care about
marriage registration now.

642
01:24:09,791 --> 01:24:11,708
I realized that possession

643
01:24:13,666 --> 01:24:16,625
is less important than
having a chance to take care of him.

644
01:24:24,791 --> 01:24:26,333
I miss him.

645
01:24:39,791 --> 01:24:41,375
So do I.

646
01:24:48,333 --> 01:24:50,291
You know?
He was so sad that night.

647
01:24:53,583 --> 01:24:55,750
He thought we didn't love him.

648
01:25:00,708 --> 01:25:03,208
He even asked me to run away with him.

649
01:25:17,083 --> 01:25:20,541
I feel like I ruined everything.

650
01:25:25,041 --> 01:25:26,333
I'm sorry.

651
01:25:28,708 --> 01:25:30,000
I'm ashamed.

652
01:25:34,458 --> 01:25:38,375
I don't even dare to see him.

653
01:25:45,291 --> 01:25:46,791
We're still fine.

654
01:25:49,541 --> 01:25:52,041
You are still his father by law.

655
01:25:56,958 --> 01:25:58,083
Perhaps,

656
01:26:00,000 --> 01:26:01,291
let's just be who we are

657
01:26:04,000 --> 01:26:05,625
and let him be who he is.

658
01:26:06,833 --> 01:26:08,041
That's enough.

659
01:26:14,875 --> 01:26:18,625
I don't believe it's impossible for us to
take care of him on our own.

660
01:27:08,291 --> 01:27:09,375
Butr…

661
01:27:11,291 --> 01:27:14,833
It's been more than a week.
Are you happy to have me?

662
01:27:16,791 --> 01:27:17,916
It's good.

663
01:27:22,333 --> 01:27:23,583
Do you love me?

664
01:27:28,916 --> 01:27:30,250
I don't know.

665
01:28:06,125 --> 01:28:10,500
No love can replace another.

666
01:28:11,750 --> 01:28:12,875
None.

667
01:28:23,541 --> 01:28:25,166
I have two fathers.

668
01:28:26,125 --> 01:28:29,291
How are Papi and Daddy
related to each other?

669
01:28:29,916 --> 01:28:33,375
My friends said my fathers are queers.

670
01:28:34,875 --> 01:28:35,958
It's nonsense.

671
01:28:37,583 --> 01:28:40,000
Both of them are the ones
who love you the most.

672
01:28:40,666 --> 01:28:42,750
How much do you love them?

673
01:28:42,833 --> 01:28:44,333
The most in the world.

674
01:28:45,208 --> 01:28:46,166
Why is that?

675
01:28:47,625 --> 01:28:49,750
I don't know, but it's so much.

676
01:28:50,916 --> 01:28:52,041
Good.

677
01:28:53,000 --> 01:28:57,875
I believe you can't imagine
how much you'll love your mom.

678
01:28:59,333 --> 01:29:03,333
But for Papi and Daddy,
you don't need to imagine at all.

679
01:29:04,666 --> 01:29:08,416
You can see and feel it every second.

680
01:29:09,416 --> 01:29:11,291
You're luckier than I am, you know.

681
01:29:11,958 --> 01:29:14,333
I grew up in an orphanage.

682
01:29:15,291 --> 01:29:17,000
What does orphan mean?

683
01:29:18,708 --> 01:29:22,458
It means a child without a mom and dad.

684
01:29:24,541 --> 01:29:27,958
Ever since I could remember,
I had to admit that I have neither.

685
01:29:28,541 --> 01:29:30,750
And what did you do?

686
01:29:34,666 --> 01:29:36,916
It might be too difficult
for a kid like you.

687
01:29:37,916 --> 01:29:42,375
But if you love what you have,
you'll have what you love.

688
01:30:08,875 --> 01:30:14,625
Who… always see you through
When you are sad?

689
01:30:15,541 --> 01:30:21,708
Who... always comfort you?

690
01:30:22,750 --> 01:30:28,541
Who… love you
More than anything?

691
01:30:28,958 --> 01:30:35,875
Their love is bigger than
The earth and sky

692
01:30:36,958 --> 01:30:43,875
If the world was a pen
And the sky was paper

693
01:30:44,625 --> 01:30:49,000
And the ocean was ink

694
01:30:49,083 --> 01:30:53,041
Those wouldn't be
Enough to declare their love

695
01:30:53,500 --> 01:30:59,250
Who… love you
As much as their lives?

696
01:31:00,500 --> 01:31:06,625
Who… are always kind to you?

697
01:31:07,416 --> 01:31:13,416
Who… love you unconditionally

698
01:31:13,541 --> 01:31:19,000
With no ill intent?
An everlasting love

699
01:31:20,000 --> 01:31:22,916
Who…?

